.Sh CONFIGURATION
Advent of Code does not exposes a proper API for tools like
.Nm .
As a result,
.Nm
interacts with the Advent of Code server using the session ID
of a logged in user.
To obtain your session ID do the following:
.Pp
.Bl -enum -offset 3n -compact
.It
log in to Advent of Code
.It
open your browserâ€™s developer tools
.It
go to the Storage tab
.It
find the cookie named
.Ql "session"
.It
copy its value to a file
.El
.Pp
The path to the file containing your session ID should be passed
to
.Fl "-session" .
By default,
.Nm
will look in the current working directory at a file called
.Eo
.Pa ./session.txt
.Ec .
.
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Nm
exits
.Ql "0"
if exiting without error.
Otherwise the exit status will be
.Ql "1" .
